creating a new dataset with necessary columns for our model. Feature engineering some new columns that will hopefully make our algorithm perform better¶

In [46]:
#creating an each game summary
nfl_stats = df_all_years.groupby(['season', 'week', 'away_team','home_team', 'posteam', 'defteam','season_type', 'home_coach','away_coach' ,'stadium', 'weather'], as_index = False).agg({'touchdown':'sum',
                                                                                                        'sack':'sum',
                                                                                                        'punt_attempt':'sum',
                                                                                                        'complete_pass':'sum', 
                                                                                                        'pass_attempt':'sum',
                                                                                                        'passing_yards':'sum',
                                                                                                        'pass_touchdown':'sum',
                                                                                                        'rushing_yards':'sum',
                                                                                                        'interception':'sum', 
                                                                                                        'series_success':'sum', 
                                                                                                        'qb_hit':'sum',
                                                                                                        'yards_gained': lambda x: x[df_all_years['sack'] == 1].sum(),
                                                                                                        'qb_epa':'mean',
                                                                                                        'air_epa':'mean',
                                                                                                        'yac_epa':'mean',
                                                                                                        'drive_time_of_possession': lambda x: x.str.split(':').apply(lambda t: int(t[0]) * 60 + int(t[1]) if isinstance(t, list) else 0).sum(),
                                                                                                        'total_home_score': 'max',
                                                                                                        'total_away_score': 'max',
                                                                                                        'total_home_rush_epa':'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_home_pass_epa':'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_away_rush_epa':'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_away_pass_epa':'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_home_comp_air_epa': 'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_home_comp_yac_epa': 'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_away_comp_air_epa': 'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_away_comp_yac_epa':'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_home_epa': 'mean',
                                                                                                        'total_away_epa':'mean',
})
In [47]:
nfl_stats.shape
Out[47]:
(5934, 39)
In [48]:
nfl_stats.rename(columns={'yards_gained': 'sack_yards'}, inplace=True)
Adding in a passing efficiency column to help our algorithm¶
In [49]:
#weights for passing efficiency column
k1 = 20
k2 = 45
k3 = 1
In [50]:
nfl_stats['team_passing_efficiency'] = (
    nfl_stats['passing_yards'] / nfl_stats['pass_attempt'] + 
    nfl_stats['pass_touchdown'] * k1 - 
    nfl_stats['interception'] * k2 +
    nfl_stats['qb_epa'] * k3

)
Smoothing columns to reduce variability. Will be shifted to make the algorithm make predictions for future games¶
In [51]:
columns_to_smooth = [ 'touchdown', 'sack', 'punt_attempt', 'complete_pass', 'pass_attempt',
       'passing_yards', 'pass_touchdown', 'rushing_yards', 'interception',
       'series_success', 'qb_hit', 'sack_yards', 'qb_epa', 'air_epa',
       'yac_epa', 'drive_time_of_possession', 'total_home_score',
       'total_away_score', 'total_home_rush_epa', 'total_home_pass_epa',
       'total_away_rush_epa', 'total_away_pass_epa', 'total_home_comp_air_epa',
       'total_home_comp_yac_epa', 'total_away_comp_air_epa',
       'total_away_comp_yac_epa', 'total_home_epa', 'total_away_epa',
       'team_passing_efficiency']

nfl_stats[[f'rolling_avg_{col}' for col in columns_to_smooth]] = (
    nfl_stats[columns_to_smooth]
    .rolling(window=3, min_periods=1)  # 5-game rolling window, min_periods avoids NaN for small sets
    .mean()
)

Creating our binary win/loss column that our model will predict¶
In [53]:
condition = [((nfl_stats['total_home_score']) > (nfl_stats['total_away_score']))]
In [54]:
values = [1]
In [55]:
nfl_stats['home_win'] = np.select(condition, values)

fig, ax = plt.subplots()

feature_names = ['_'.join(feature_name.split('_')[3:]) for feature_name in features]

coef_ = log_model.coef_[0]

features_coef_sorted = sorted(zip(features, coef_), key=lambda x:x[-1], reverse=True)

features_sorted = [feature for feature, _ in features_coef_sorted]
coef_sorted = [coef for _, coef in features_coef_sorted]

ax.set_title('Feature importance')

ax.barh(features_sorted, coef_sorted);

y_pred_proba = log_model# Now, let's try to draw the ROC curve for class y=1
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc, roc_auc_score

# Calculate the fpr/tpr 
y_pred_proba = log_model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[::,1]
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_proba)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

# Do plot
plt.figure()
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, color="orange", linewidth=2,
    label="ROC curve (area = %0.2f)" % roc_auc)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color="navy", linewidth=2, linestyle="--")
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
plt.title("ROC for class y=1")
plt.legend(loc="lower right")

In [ ]:
params = {
    "loss" : ["hinge", "log", "squared_hinge", "modified_huber", "perceptron"],
    "alpha" : [0.0001, 0.001, 0.01, 0.1],
    "penalty" : ["l2", "l1", "elasticnet", "none"],
}

#create the model
SGDC_model = SGDClassifier(random_state=42, max_iter=1000, tol=1e-3)
grid_SGDC = GridSearchCV(SGDC_model, param_grid=params, cv=5, scoring='accuracy', verbose=3)

#fit the model
grid_SGDC.fit(X_scaled, y)

print(grid_SGDC.best_params_) 
print(grid_SGDC.best_estimator_)

In [ ]:
def evaluate_model(name, y_true, y_pred):
    print(f"\n🧪 Evaluation for {name}:")
    print("Accuracy :", accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred))
    print("F1 Score :", f1_score(y_true, y_pred))
    print("Precision:", precision_score(y_true, y_pred))
    print("Recall   :", recall_score(y_true, y_pred))
    print("\nClassification Report:\n", classification_report(y_true, y_pred))
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues')
    plt.title(f'Confusion Matrix: {name}')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.ylabel('Actual')
    plt.show()

In [ ]:
rf_probs = rf_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
xgb_probs = xgb_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
grid_probs = grid_svc2.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:,1]
log_probs = log_model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:,1]

fpr_grid, tpr_grid, _ = roc_curve(y_test, grid_probs)
fpr_rf, tpr_rf, _ = roc_curve(y_test, rf_probs)
fpr_xgb, tpr_xgb, _ = roc_curve(y_test, xgb_probs)
fpr_log, tpr_log, _ = roc_curve(y_test, log_probs)

plt.plot(fpr_grid, tpr_grid, label='GridSearch (AUC = {:.2f})'.format(roc_auc_score(y_test, grid_probs)))
plt.plot(fpr_rf, tpr_rf, label='Random Forest (AUC = {:.2f})'.format(roc_auc_score(y_test, rf_probs)))
plt.plot(fpr_xgb, tpr_xgb, label='XGBoost (AUC = {:.2f})'.format(roc_auc_score(y_test, xgb_probs)))
plt.plot(fpr_log, tpr_log, label='Logistic Regression (AUC = {:.2f})'.format(roc_auc_score(y_test, log_probs)))
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')  # Diagonal line
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
This concludes the NFL game prediction project. The best-performing algorithm was the GridSearch-optimized SVC, which achieved the highest accuracy, F1 score, and recall. In contrast, XGBoost was the weakest performer overall.¶
There is still significant work to be done to improve the model’s accuracy. Future efforts could focus on additional feature engineering to strengthen weakly correlated features or remove irrelevant ones altogether. Incorporating new variables, such as weather conditions and player injuries, may also provide deeper insight into team performance and further enhance prediction accuracy.¶
